The tool is two files: mycelium.sh and SKILL.md. Everything else
in this repo is how WE develop the tool — our tests, our spec, our
decision log, our hooks, our gitleaks config, our notes.

A new user copies mycelium.sh (and optionally SKILL.md for their
agents). They start with an empty notes ref and build their own
culture. They don't inherit our values, our warnings, our decisions.

The hooks/ directory contains examples of best practices — things
we recommend but don't require. gitleaks scanning, awareness hooks.
A user can adopt them, adapt them, or ignore them.

This distinction must stay clear as the repo grows. The tool must
not accumulate project-specific assumptions.
